  "text": "Of note, there has never been a report on gene mutations in SFTPC in COPD patients. This strengthens the evidence that these dominantly expressed mutations are disease-causing for IP [CITATION_1] . Although more than 60 SFTPC gene mutations have been detected and associated with specified or unspecified ILD, a comprehensive analysis of the lung phenotypes including surfactant-BAL profiles from affected patients as well as of the detailed molecular pathomechanisms resulting from these mutated SP-C proteins remain still elusive for many BRICHOS domain-(e. g. L110R, P115L, A116D, A112T) and non-BRICHOS domain-SFTPC mutations. We hypothesize that alveolar epithelial ER stress is present in all of these familial ILD patients.",
